          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Targets wheels accommodating 6 metallic Bi targets on",
                "a 3 mu-m Al backing were used. The average thickness of",
                "the Bi target segments on a given wheel varied from",
                "0.38 to 0.51 mg/cm2 + -0.02 mg/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " GABRIELA detector array was used to detect the",
                "residues and their subsequent alpha decay or fission",
                "as well as gamma rays, X rays and conversion",
                "electrons. The evaporation residues pass through a",
                "Time of Flight detector composed of 2 emissive foils",
                "and 4 large-size (70x90 mm2) micro channel plate",
                "detectors. The residues are then implanted into a",
                "10x10 cm2 300 mu-m thick Double-sided Silicon Strip",
                "Detector. Particles escaping from the DSSD are",
                "detected in eight 6x5 cm2 DSSDs with 16 strips on each",
                "side."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "The Ge array consists of a large clover detector",
                "installed just behind the DSSD and 4 coaxial detectors",
                "forming a cross around the DSSD."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "OLMS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Separator for Heavy Elements Spectroscopy",
                " (SHELS) was used for separation of fusion-evaporation",
                "reaction products."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "ASPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By author* The data were taken in two experiments.",
                "The first experiment was performed in two campaigns.",
                "During the first campaign, cyclotron beam energies of",
                "255 and 265 MeV were used, while in second the",
                "primary beam energies were 255 and 275 MeV. For the",
                "second experiment, primary beam energies of 255, 265",
                "and 275 MeV were used.",
                "Cross sections were averaged over the first and second",
                "experiments. Mid-target energies are given."
              ]
            }
          ],
